%I A396564 #21 Jun 09 2026 21:00:56
%S A396564 30,62,174,198,238,357,432,1146,1305,3382
%N A396564 Integers x such that there exist four integers 0<x<=y<=z and 0<t<=w such that sigma(x)^2*psi(x) = sigma(y)^2*psi(y) = sigma(z)^2*psi(z) = x^3 + y^3 + z^3 + t^3 + w^3.
%C A396564 The numbers x, y, z, t and w form a sigma^2*psi-cubic quintuple.
%H A396564 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://hal.science/hal-05303937">On σψ-quadratic k-tuples and related generalizations</a>, hal-05303937, 2025.
%H A396564 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-2psi-cubic-quintuples/blob/main/A396564">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A396564 (174, 190, 323, 5, 94) is such a quintuple because sigma(174)^2 * psi(174) = sigma(190)^2 * psi(190) = sigma(323)^2 * psi(323) = 360^2 * 360 = 174^3 + 190^3 + 323^3 + 5^3 + 94^3.
%o A396564 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A396564 Cf. A000203, A001615, A003328, A386378, A391535, A396309, A396459.
%K A396564 nonn,more
